## 4. Requirements

### 4.1 Business Requirements

Business requirements describe what business outcome or capability is needed. They should not describe screens, APIs, detailed workflows, technical design, performance thresholds, or implementation behavior.

| BR ID | Business Requirement | Business Outcome | Priority | Source / Driver |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| BR-001 | [The business needs to achieve / enable / comply with ...] | [Outcome] | [Must / Should / Could / Won't] | DR-001 |

### 4.2 Stakeholder Requirements

Stakeholder requirements describe what a stakeholder group needs in order for the business requirement to be satisfied. Detailed system functions belong in the FR template.

| SR ID | Stakeholder Requirement | Stakeholder / User Group | Linked BR ID | Priority |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| SR-001 | [Stakeholder needs to ...] | [Group] | BR-001 | [Must / Should / Could / Won't] |

### 4.3 Transition Requirements

Transition requirements describe temporary business needs required to move from current state to future state.

| TR ID | Transition Requirement | Type | Linked BR ID | Owner |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| TR-001 | [Training, migration, cutover, readiness, communication, decommissioning, or temporary support need] | [Type] | BR-001 | [Role] |

